Ad Text:
Permanent/continuing, full-time appointment

Attractive remuneration package

The Financial Services & Enterprise Data Division delivers strategic financial leadership and operational support to enable the University’s academic, research, and community objectives. Our division includes key units such as Institutional Research Accounting, Data and Analytics, Procurement, Operations and Research Accounting, Treasury, and Subsidiary and Customer Accounting. Together, we ensure financial sustainability, compliance, and efficient resource allocation across the institution.

About the Role

In this role, you will lead the development and implementation of AI and automation solutions to enhance operational efficiency across the University. Working collaboratively with Finance, IT, and other key stakeholders, you will integrate innovative technologies that support the University’s financial objectives. You will also manage AI governance, ensure compliance with relevant standards, and facilitate training to staff on new tools and processes.

About You

The successful candidate will hold a relevant degree (or equivalent) and be an experienced practitioner capable of working independently and leading others. You will have proven experience in planning and managing resources to achieve defined objectives, as well as strong analytical skills to collect and interpret data for informed decision-making. Your expertise will include developing change strategies based on gap analysis and readiness assessments, conducting business requirements analysis, and documenting current-state processes within a complex organisational context. Proficiency in application development and a solid understanding of AI, machine learning, and automation technologies—along with their practical application in business operations and process improvement—are essential.

Position Description

For further information please contact Matthew Wright, Chief Financial Officer on (02) 4221 5737.

How to Apply

 Applicants are requested to submit a CV and cover letter.  The cover letter should be no more than 3 pages, summarising your skills and experience as they relate to the selection criteria located in the position description.

 Closing Date:  Monday 26 January 2026, 11:59 PM

Note: Visa sponsorship is not available for this position.  Only candidates with valid work rights in Australia are eligible to apply.

At RAA, we’ve been trusted by South Australians for over 120 years. We’re more than just a household name—we’re an organisation that thrives on innovation, collaboration, and delivering value to our members every day. Now, we’re looking for a Principal Data Engineer to lead the way in building scalable, sustainable, and secure data solutions that power our future.

Why you’ll love working with us:

Iconic organisation: Be part of one of SA’s most recognised and respected brands.

Flexible hybrid work: Balance your career and lifestyle with flexible arrangements.

Impactful leadership: Shape the future of our enterprise data platforms and mentor a talented team.

Collaborative culture: Work alongside senior specialists and business leaders who value fast delivery, innovation, and governance.

Continuous growth: Access professional development, mentoring opportunities, and cutting-edge technologies.

What you’ll do:

As our Principal Data Engineer, you’ll:

Advocate data strategy with stakeholders and collaborate to plan initiative delivery

Partner with business stakeholders to translate complex data demands into deliverables.

Provide technical leadership, guiding a team of data engineers to deliver high-value solutions.

Lead the design and delivery of scalable, secure, and sustainable data platform solutions.

Champion data governance and best practice engineering, ensuring integrity, performance, and compliance.

Drive operational excellence, identifying opportunities for optimisation and embedding self-healing solutions.

What we’re looking for:

We’re seeking a seasoned professional with:

15+ years’ experience specialising in data engineering, SQL database development, or BI engineering.

Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, IT, or equivalent (preferred)

Strong specialisation in database development, analytics data platforms, data transformation, data governance, CI/CD and DevOps.

Deep expertise in building analytical data warehousing and data marts with complex data sets.

Proven leadership in guiding teams, planning initiatives, and delivering enterprise-scale solutions.

Strong technical skills in AWS Snowflake, Microsoft Azure, SQL Server, dbt, SSIS, and CI/CD practices.

Exceptional communication skills—able to simplify complex technical concepts and engage stakeholders.

A passion for collaboration, innovation, transformation and building sustainable data solutions.

About us

We’re proud to be one of South Australia’s most iconic brands, trusted by members for more than 120 years. SA born-and-bred, RAA might be best known for our road service and insurance products, but we’re excited to be continuously diversifying to better help our members and community.

Our goal? To make life better for South Australians. That’s why we’re proud to offer a range of services to our 820,000+ members, including travel, energy, solar and battery, electric vehicle charging, our RAA Rewards program and more. With motoring still a priority, we’re just as passionate as we were in 1903 about road safety, advocating for a safer SA into the future.

We’re also one of the state’s largest employers, with more than 1100 employees working across our local sites at Mile End, RAA Place (CBD) and Adelaide Airport and our many retail and travel shops. With new office spaces in the city and city fringe in the works, and a buzzing people-first culture, we’re proud to be the State’s #1 Employer Brand.

Benefits

We love our people at RAA and believe our employees should be rewarded for being a part of the RAA family. Some of our employee benefits include:

Free RAA premium road service

Access to our RAA Rewards Program  

Generous discounts on all RAA products

Flexible work arrangements

Ongoing Training & Development opportunities and a Study Support Program

Wellbeing facilities and Corporate Health Insurance Plan

How to apply

To be part of something bigger and work for a passionate South Australian organisation with members at heart click ‘Apply’ to submit your application by 9.00am Monday, 26th January 2026.

You'll need to provide evidence of your eligibility to work in Australia and we'll also need you to undertake a police check before you can work with us at RAA.

That's why we encourage applications from everyone, including people living with disability, job seekers of all ages, First Nations Peoples, members of the LGBTIQA+ community and people from culturally diverse backgrounds.

About the Role

The Finance Transformation Lead plays a critical role in delivering the finance transformation agenda across the region. Reporting to the Head of Finance Transformation this role is responsible for driving process improvement, supporting systems implementation, and embedding scalable, best-practice finance ways of working.

This role will suit a hands-on finance transformation professional who enjoys working close to delivery. You will partner closely with Finance, Technology, and Operations stakeholders, acting as both a problem-solver and change agent to translate transformation priorities into practical outcomes.

Key Job Responsibilities

Finance Transformation & Process Improvement

Deliver finance transformation initiatives across regional operations, including process redesign, standardisation, and automation.
Analyse existing finance processes, identify inefficiencies, and design improved, scalable solutions.
Support continuous improvement initiatives to enhance efficiency, control, and insight across finance.
Systems & Digital Enablement

Support the implementation, optimisation, and ongoing enhancement of finance systems, including ERP, reporting, and automation tools.
Work closely with Technology and Digital teams to ensure solutions meet business and finance requirements.
Contribute to the uplift of finance data, reporting, and analytics capability.
Stakeholder Engagement & Business Partnering

Partner with stakeholders across Finance, Technology, Development, and Operations to embed new processes and systems.
Support senior leaders in driving adoption of new ways of working across a geographically dispersed business.
Act as a key point of contact for finance transformation initiatives within assigned workstreams.
Delivery & Execution

Operate as a hands-on contributor, owning delivery of defined workstreams and initiatives.
Manage competing priorities and timelines to ensure delivery to scope and quality.
Support change management, documentation, and training to ensure sustainable outcomes.
Ideal Background

Proven experience in finance transformation, financial systems, process improvement, or related roles.
Hands-on exposure to finance systems implementation or optimisation (ERP, automation, reporting tools, finance processes standardisation).
Experience within large, complex organisations (typically $500m+ turnover), ideally within infrastructure, real assets, technology, or capital-intensive environments.
Excellent communication skills and ability to engage with a broad stakeholder group.
CA / CPA qualified (or equivalent) preferred.
Background in finance, FP&A, financial systems, or consulting environments advantageous.

The role

This role sits at the heart of how technology risk data is captured, governed and turned into meaningful insight. You’ll own and optimise our enterprise GRC system, ensuring it’s reliable, well-governed and genuinely useful for the business.

Operating in a Line 2 capacity, you’ll work closely with technology and risk stakeholders to uplift reporting, strengthen data integrity, and provide thoughtful challenge across key technology risk areas. It’s a hands-on role with real influence, ideal for someone who enjoys blending systems, data and risk expertise.

 

Position Accountabilities 

In this role, you will:

Own the day-to-day management and optimisation of the enterprise GRC platform
Manage system configuration, user access, workflows and data structures
Act as the go-to expert for GRC system queries, enhancements and issue resolution
Strengthen data quality through controls, validation checks and reconciliation processes
Support integrations and data movements between risk systems and broader enterprise platforms
Provide second-line oversight and challenge across technology and data risk practices
Contribute to reviews, audits and control assurance activities within Technology Risk
Develop strong system reporting and insights that support risk decision-making

 

What experience you’ll bring

You’ll bring a mix of technical capability, risk awareness and stakeholder confidence, including:

Experience working in data, reporting, analytics or systems roles within risk, compliance or technology environments
Hands-on exposure to GRC platforms (RSA Archer or similar highly regarded)
Strong grounding in data quality, governance, lineage and control concepts
Familiarity with technology risk, data risk or enterprise risk frameworks in regulated environments
Confidence working with reporting and analysis tools such as Power BI, BigQuery or SQL
A practical mindset, comfortable balancing detail with commercial outcomes
Relevant qualifications in IT, business, finance or a related discipline


Location –Toowong

Close to a variety of public transport and easy parking options, the Toowong office has excellent end of trip facilities (including secure bike storage and showers), outdoor spaces and plenty of modern collaborative areas to work and connect with colleagues. 

Conveniently based at Toowong Village tower with views of the mountains and the Brisbane River, our location is only 4 km from the city and provides access to retail, restaurants and other amenities.

 

The benefits of working at A&G

Be rewarded - we recognise high performance and reward our people for their hard work through bonuses and other perks.
Work flexibility - with options to work from home up to two days per week.
Options for leave - life happens, so we’ve got volunteer days, an additional paid ‘ME’ day, paid parental leave and the opportunity to purchase additional leave to cover all of the big stuff.
Grow with us - we’ve got learning and professional development opportunities to suit everyone.
Give back - our A&G Difference program gives you the power to change our community for the better through volunteering, fundraising and donation opportunities for causes that you’re passionate about.
Take care of yourself - your wellbeing is important to us and our healthy mind and body hub, mental-health support and fitness discounts will help you be your best self.
Celebrate the wins - we love sharing our successes and celebrating together - join us and you’ve got a ticket to our many on-site events throughout the year, family fun days and annual celebrations.
Save money - as well as discounts on insurance products, we’ve teamed up with some incredible retailers, hospitality providers and others to bring you discounts on your purchases, no matter where you are in Australia.

 

About us

Auto & General (A&G) is the fastest-growing major Motor and Home insurer in Australia, providing insurance products and solutions to safeguard a brighter future for our customers and community.  

Our range of general insurance products including Car, Motorcycle, Home, Contents Pet and Travel products are delivered through our multi-award-winning brand Budget Direct and partnerships with leading brands - ING, Qantas, Virgin Money and Coles Insurance.

We’re excited about the future and we’re always on the lookout for talented, passionate individuals who can help us achieve our goal of being Australia’s best insurer! If this sounds like you, apply today.

 

Auto & General values individual differences and believes in fostering an inclusive culture that creates a great place to work for all.

About the Opportunity 

Sigma Healthcare is proudly powering pharmacy, operating Australia’s largest pharmacy network through trusted brands including Chemist Warehouse, Amcal and Discount Drug Stores, supported by a leading full line wholesale and distribution business serving pharmacies nationwide. 

Following our merger, we are entering an exciting new phase of growth as a Top 50 ASX listed organisation. 

As part of this evolution, we’re building a dedicated Commercial Finance portfolio partnering closely with our Marketing and Merchandise teams moving beyond traditional reporting into genuine commercial influence. 

This Senior Financial Analyst is a key individual contributor position within this portfolio, supporting some of the most commercially critical areas of the business. 

Reporting to the Finance Manager, you’ll partner closely with Merchandise and Marketing leaders to deliver insight led analysis, support margin and investment decisions, and improve overall trading performance. 

Key Responsibilities 

Partner with Merchandise and Marketing leaders to interpret trading performance and support commercial decision making 

Support the month end close, reporting and analysis for Merchandise and Marketing portfolios 

Deliver detailed financial and commercial insights across sales, margin, volume, pricing, mix and COGS 

Assess promotional effectiveness and marketing return on investment 

Prepare high quality monthly performance reporting for senior leadership 

Review financial and non-financial data to identify trends, risks and opportunities 

Support budgeting, forecasting and rolling forecast processes 

Contribute to the continuous improvement of finance processes, systems and BI 

Build strong stakeholder relationships across Commercial and Finance teams 


About You 

To succeed in this role, you’ll bring: 

CA / CPA qualification and a tertiary qualification in Finance 

3–5 years’ experience in commercial finance or financial analysis 

Experience partnering with Marketing and/or Merchandise teams (retail, FMCG or wholesale preferred) 

Advanced Excel skills (Power BI experience is desirable) 

Strong analytical capability with the ability to translate data into clear insights 

Confident communication and stakeholder management skills 

A proactive, curious and commercially minded approach 

 Why Join Us? 

At Sigma Healthcare, our people make the difference. Here’s what you can expect: 

A high impact Senior Financial Analyst role partnering with Marketing and Merchandise 

The opportunity to contribute to a newly established Commercial Finance portfolio 

Genuine exposure to senior leaders and commercially complex decision-making 

Join a Top 50 ASX listed organisation at an exciting stage of transformation 

Hybrid working arrangements 

Career development opportunities as the Commercial Finance function continues to evolve 


Apply Now 

If you’re looking for a commercially focused Senior Financial Analyst role where you can influence outcomes and deliver meaningful insights, we’d love to hear from you. 

Apply now and help shape the future of Commercial Finance at Sigma Healthcare.

The Company

Inspired by Australia's great people and amazing foodie culture, Chobani USA purchased the Gippsland Dairy brand to form Chobani Australia in 2011. Flash forward 12 years and Chobani is Australia’s #1 yogurt brand, living in the hearts (and tummies) of fans across the country.

At Chobani it’s always been about more than yogurt. Access to delicious and nutritious food should be a right, not a privilege, Chobani’s purpose as a leading food and drink manufacturer is to use their platforms, their resources and their influence to bridge that gap, to make a difference in the fight against food insecurity.

  

The Opportunity

As we enter a phase of accelerated sales growth and capacity expansion, we are seeking an experienced Integrated Business Planning (IBP) Manager to lead and mature our IBP capability.

In this pivotal role, you will own and facilitate the end-to-end IBP process, acting as a trusted business partner across Demand Planning, Supply Chain, Commercial, Finance, and Data & Analytics. You will drive cross-functional alignment around a single, integrated plan that supports financial performance, customer service excellence, and sustainable growth.

With strong commercial acumen, you will operate confidently across the P&L, enabling informed trade-off decisions and providing robust governance around capacity and capital investment planning. You will play a key role in embedding best-practice IBP processes that are fit-for-purpose, scalable, and consistently applied in a fast-paced, agile FMCG environment.

This role is ideal for a high-impact IBP professional with relevant integrated planning experience, ideally within FMCG or food manufacturing, who thrives on influence, data-driven decision-making, and driving business-wide change.

 

Skills & Experience

Ideally to be successful in the role you will: 

Proven commercial leader with strong IBP best-practice expertise in an FMCG environment (food industry experience highly regarded).

Demonstrated ability to influence senior stakeholders and drive higher-quality decision-making through a disciplined, closed-loop IBP process.

Highly adept at synthesising complex inputs from multiple sources into clear, actionable insights and a compelling narrative that drives alignment and action.

Strategic thinker with the ability to see the end-to-end enterprise picture and connect data, assumptions, and trade-offs into an integrated IBP framework.

Passionate about continuous improvement, with the confidence to challenge the status quo and elevate planning maturity across the business.

 

This critical role is suited to a highly collaborative, systems thinker who can connect the dots across the business and bring stakeholders on the journey to build a best-in-class planning capability. You will thrive on influencing key decision-makers, constructively challenging the status quo, and driving meaningful improvement, underpinned by a genuine passion for continuous improvement and change.

In return, you’ll be rewarded with truly passionate people who love what they do and bring their true and authentic selves to work every day. The role will be based at our modern Dandenong South office, where you will have access to a 3/2 hybrid work model, free parking and unlimited free yoghurt whilst in the office!




Benefits

At Chobani, making a difference is in our DNA and that means you will be joining an organisation that is constantly seeking to drive positive change for the community, people, and planet. Chobani offer flexible working arrangements, excellent benefits including up to $1000 in furniture to set up your work from home Chobani Office, a wellbeing program and a great rewards and recognition program.

Job Overview


The Intuit Global Business Solutions Group (GBSG) is responsible for generating over half of Intuit’s global revenue. Flagship brands include QuickBooks and Mailchimp, and our vision is to power SMB prosperity globally by delivering our AI-enabled 'all-in-one' platform in one place for small and mid-sized businesses to run and grow their business, from lead to cash, with a virtual team of AI-enabled agents and human experts.

The roll out of a more powerful, platform-backed Quickbooks across 100+ countries last November marked a pivotal milestone, and it also proved something critical: while tax codes, regulations and languages change at the border, the fundamental needs of small businesses do not. No matter the location, our customers need to get paid, manage capital, and find customers.

The International Product Organization, part of the GBSG, is seeking a dynamic product leader to translate global platform capabilities into regional market growth. Reporting to the VP of Product, International, this leader will be a critical part of the APAC Senior Leadership team, working closely with the Regional Commercial VP acting as the bridge between Intuit’s global platform and the local realities of the APAC markets.

Your mission is twofold: drive aggressive customer growth and service adoption in established markets while architecting the 'innovation engine' that streamlines the complexity of the next phase of regional expansion. You will transform fragmented market requirements into locally-relevant, integrated platform-based solutions that scale seamlessly for small and mid-market businesses across the region.

Responsibilities

APAC Product Vision & Growth Strategy: Architect and execute the end-to-end product strategy for the APAC region. You will harmonize localized customer needs with Intuit’s global platform to drive aggressive acquisition, deepen service adoption, and maximize regional P&L performance.

Strategic Market Expansion & Opportunity Mapping: Act as the lead scout for new market entry. By synthesizing macroeconomic trends, regulatory shifts, and SMB data, you will identify and prioritize the "next horizon" of international markets, building the 0-1 framework for successful expansion.

Localized Innovation & Roadmap Authority: Transform rigorous analysis of APAC-specific pain points—from micro-businesses to mid-market enterprises—into a high-velocity product roadmap. You ensure that regional requirements are not just "met," but are leveraged as competitive advantages.

Commercial Strategy & Revenue Velocity: Partner with the APAC leadership team to define and deploy integrated GTM strategies, including localized pricing, packaging, and ecosystem hooks. You are responsible for ensuring our product value proposition resonates across diverse European and emerging markets to fuel sustainable revenue growth.

Organizational Leadership & Cultural Excellence: Build and mentor a world-class product organization that balances high-quality craft with speed. You will foster a culture of customer obsession and operational rigor, ensuring regional delivery plans align perfectly with Intuit’s overarching global mission.

Ecosystem Intelligence & Competitive Defence: Serve as the regional authority on industry trends and competitor movement. You will utilize data-driven insights to proactively pivot the roadmap, neutralizing threats and capturing first-mover advantages in the rapidly evolving fintech and AI landscape.

Qualifications

The Head of Product, APAC will bring expertise in international product, product go to market and/or corporate strategy to drive our global growth by identifying international markets to prioritize, evaluating product market fit, launching new markets, and driving.

Domain

The ideal candidate has 10-12+ years of relevant product and or product strategy experience.

Prior experience leading global/international expansion strategy, ideally with a focus on Europe.

Experience building for SMB and mid-market customers at a company with an ecosystem of products and services.

Proven experience in harmonizing product strategies across diverse offerings (e.g., finance, marketing, payments) to build a unified customer ecosystem.

Demonstrated success leveraging advanced technologies (AI/ML) to solve complex customer problems, especially in areas like localization, compliance, or predictive insights.

Proven track record of successfully championing trajectory-changing business shifts for organizations, including commercial and product innovation that translates to revenue and customer growth.

Known for driving durable revenue growth that balances short and long-term investments.

Experience in building and executing a clear, crisp, durable 3-year product strategy.

Functional

Exceptional at prioritization and decision-making -- narrowing to the critical few.

Experience managing a complex portfolio of products with both 0-1 offerings and existing at-scale offerings.

Effective at working cross-functionally in a large matrix-style organization to ensure teams can move with speed and maximum impact.

Exceptional problem-solving skills and ability to translate complex data into actionable insights.

Expertise in translating complex regional regulatory and compliance requirements (e.g., VAT, payroll, GDPR) into non-negotiable, locally relevant product roadmaps.

Leadership And Managerial

Exceptional ability to influence beyond their direct team to the portfolio level, company, and executive leadership level, including cross-functional partners and potential stakeholders.

Experience managing teams that cover more than one primary offering.

Experience successfully attracting and retaining top talent globally, including experience managing teams across multiple global locations.

Intuit provides a competitive compensation package with a strong pay for performance rewards approach. This position may be eligible for a cash bonus, equity rewards and benefits, in accordance with our applicable plans and programs (see more about our compensation and benefits at Intuit®: Careers | Benefits). Pay offered is based on factors such as job-related knowledge, skills, experience, and work location. The opportunity

Support acquisition underwriting and project evaluation
Perform sensitivity analysis, scenario modelling and stress testing
Analyse funding structures, returns and project economics
Assist with investment papers, board materials and decision packs
Continuously improve modelling frameworks and assumptions
Provide commercial insights to senior stakeholders
About you

This role will suit someone who is genuinely strong in financial modelling – not just comfortable with it.

Investment analysis
Corporate finance / transaction services / advisory
Development feasibilities or property analysis
Infrastructure or project finance
Valuations or modelling teams
You will ideally have:

Advanced Excel skills (essential)
Strong experience building 3-way models from scratch
A highly analytical and logical mindset
A degree in Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Engineering or similar
Strong attention to detail
The ability to translate numbers into clear commercial insights
Why this role?
High-impact, decision-facing position
Exposure to real capital deployment and development projects
Strong learning curve and career progression
Work closely with senior investment and development leaders

About the Role

We are seeking an experienced and proactive Senior Business Analyst, supporting our business data, reporting, and operational improvement initiatives. This role is critical in shaping how data, insights, and operational logic come together across our contract-driven business.

 

Reporting into the CIO, you will work closely with stakeholders across operations, finance, customer teams, and leadership, you will help shape how data is captured, interpreted, and used to drive performance. This role requires someone who can think strategically, understand the broader business context, and translate complex requirements into clear, actionable insights and reporting solutions.

 

This role is suited to someone who is commercially aware, quick to understand new concepts, and able to challenge assumptions while strengthening the businesses data-driven culture.

 

The value of this position lies in understanding -

Why we need the data
What commercial or operational question we are trying to answer
How different datasets should come together to tell the right story
Which processes and data structures must be designed for accuracy, efficiency, and commercial performance

Key Responsibilities

Partner with senior stakeholders to understand business challenges and commercial drivers , translating them into structured requirements, insights, and solution pathways.
Lead complex business analysis activities including process mapping, gap analysis, problem definition, and identifying improvement opportunities.
Design and deliver Power BI dashboards and reports that drive operational and financial visibility, decision-making, and performance improvement.
Translate complex business questions into insight frameworks that you can then convert into dashboards and automated reporting.
Conduct deep-dive data analysis, root-cause investigation, and performance trend identification to support strategic decisions.
Document requirements, user stories, acceptance criteria, business rules, and process maps to support technology initiatives.
Analyse data sources and determine how they should integrate to create accurate, commercially meaningful reporting.
Contribute to business cases, cost/benefit analysis, and ongoing benefits realisation tracking for major initiatives.
Work closely with the CIO and data teams to ensure reporting aligns with our enterprise data model, Data Warehouse, and governance standards.
Collaborate with finance to align reporting outputs with financial structures, budgets, forecasting frameworks, and KPIs.
Support project delivery across testing, stakeholder validation, communication, and change management activities.
Act as a thought partner to the business, identifying opportunities, challenging existing practices, and proposing data-driven improvements. 

Skills & Experience

Essential:

5+ years’ experience in business analysis, commercial analysis, operational insights, or similar roles.
Strong reporting and analytical capability, including practical experience building Power BI dashboards, data models, and meaningful visual insights.
Excellent critical thinking and problem-solving skills, able to break down ambiguity and propose structured, strategic solutions.
Demonstrated ability to operate proactively, identifying issues, risks, and opportunities before they are escalated.
Strong business acumen with the ability to quickly understand how different parts of the organisation operate and interact.
Experience preparing business cases, cost/benefit assessments, and supporting benefits realisation.
High standard of documentation, including process maps, workflows, and user stories.
Strong communication and stakeholder management skills, able to influence decisions and collaborate across operational and corporate teams.

Beneficial:

Experience with Facility Management or Facilities Services operations, how contracts are structured, invoiced, fulfilled, measured, and renewed.
Understanding of financial reporting (P&L, budgeting, forecasting, cost centres).
Familiarity with ERP, CRM, workforce management, or operational reporting systems.
Exposure to data warehouse environments or enterprise reporting platforms.

Why Join Us?

Play a pivotal role in shaping the organisation’s data and insights strategy.
Work closely with the CIO and senior leadership on transformative digital, operational, and commercial initiatives.
Lead the thinking behind how the business measures success and understands performance.
High-impact role directly influencing contract performance, operational excellence, and service delivery.
Strong leadership visibility, autonomy, and room for intellectual ownership.
Hybrid working arrangements and a collaborative environment.

Job Title: Senior Manager P and C Data and AI Governance and Delivery
Ad Text:
Job Expectations


We have an exciting opportunity at nbn for a Senior Manager P&C Data & AI Governance and Delivery. This role will report to the Executive Manager P&C Digital Transformation.

A bit about your role

This role will lead the development and execution of nbn’s People & Culture data strategy and roadmap, shaping how people data is governed, protected and used responsibly across the organisation. You will play a central to embedding strong data governance within P&C, particularly given the sensitivity of people data, guiding everything from system access and audit processes to security reviews, approvals and capability uplift across the business.

You will support the identification and development of high‑value data and AI use cases, partnering with teams to enhance reporting, refine insights and contribute to the delivery of nbn’s One Model analytics platform. This will see you steering the P&C Data & AI roadmap, drive the delivery of prototypes of advanced AI and machine learning concepts, and identifying opportunities for automation using emerging tools. You will also champion Responsible AI practices, setting guardrails that ensure people data is used safely, ethically and with care.

Through your leadership, nbn will strengthen the integrity, capability and potential of its people data and AI ecosystem, enabling decisions that support the growth, wellbeing and impact of our workforce.

A bit about you

You bring deep experience in data and analytics, with a strong expertise in data governance and a proven ability to balance oversight with practical delivery. You are detail‑oriented and confident working with sensitive information, ensuring accuracy, compliance and care in every aspect of your work. Your technical background spans a range of data platforms and tools, and you are comfortable working with enterprise analytics environments, including One Model.

You build trusted relationships across diverse stakeholder groups, guiding them with clarity through the responsibilities, opportunities and risks that come with managing people data and AI‑enabled solutions. You bring a curious, forward‑looking mindset, and you enjoy turning strategy into action whether you are shaping new reports, developing data products, experimenting with AI and machine learning prototypes, or exploring opportunities for automation.

Life at nbn

To be part of nbn is to be part of something bigger. There’s so much more from here. Our pioneering spirit drives us forward every day. Together, we help lift the digital capability of the nation by building and connecting Australia’s best fibre infrastructure into homes and businesses, plus places and things, everywhere. We’re continuing to create Australia’s network—a network made for more. Not just a way for everyone to do the things they love but transforming the way they do them.

A more inclusive working world

nbn is committed to an inclusive, flexible, and supportive workplace where everyone can feel heard, valued, and respected. We believe diverse perspectives are the key to unlocking greater outcomes and encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities, abilities, and cultures. That's why we have a Reconciliation Action Plan, Accessibility & Inclusion Plan, offer 18 weeks of paid parental leave, are a Pride in Diversity Gold Employer for three years running, and have active employee-led diversity pillars. Click here to see our list of employee benefits and why we're recognised as a WORK180 Endorsed Employer for Women, and their Employer of Choice for 2025.

Equal Opportunities for All 

We champion equal opportunities for all employees. If you have any accessibility requirements and would like to discuss adjustments for the recruitment process, please don’t hesitate to contact us by emailing recruitment@nbnco.com.au or calling our Recruitment Accessibility Enquiry Line at +61 2 8918 9990. Please note, this line is dedicated to accessibility-related enquiries for the purposes of recruitment, and only enquiries related to accessibility adjustments will be answered. For other matters, please visit our Contact Us page on our website.

Where to from here?

Please note that this role is a permanent opportunity and applications will close at midnight on Tuesday, 27th January 2026.

What you’ll be doing

Assist with scenario analysis and cost/benefit assessments

Maintain and support project progress reporting and finance tracking with the Finance Business Partner

About you

To succeed in this role, you’ll be quick to learn, highly organised, and comfortable working in a regulated environment with new terminology and a steep initial learning curve. You take ownership of your work, ask smart questions, and maintain exceptional attention to detail.

3–5 years’ experience in financial analysis, management accounting, and/or cost modelling
Solid understanding of cost accounting principles and delivery requirements
Excel modelling capability (intermediate–level) including complex formulas, pivot tables and data visualisation (no macros required)
High attention to detail and ability to follow instructions and standards precisely
Strong analytical and structured problem-solving skills
Collaborative working style and ability to engage across technical and finance stakeholders

Dogs, cats, budgies and everything in between - pets deserve the world. They make us want to be better humans. That’s why we’ve made it our mission to build the most engaged and passionate community of pets and pet parents across the world. And we’re looking for talented team mates who can help us do it.

Founded in Sydney, our team of 500+ pet obsessives span Australia, New Zealand and the Philippines. We’ve scaled to become one of Australia's top five eComm companies and the no.1 online pet store. But we’re just getting started. Like a whippet who’s spotted their mate across the dog park, our growth is only going to accelerate, as we continue to disrupt the way that pet parents shop.

Excitingly, the pet industry is booming (as in $15 billion kind of booming) and online pet retail is set to grow exponentially in the next five years. So this is a unique career opportunity to be part of our epic growth story.

The opportunity

This Data Analytics Lead will play a key role in building and analysing models that help inform customer and operational decisions, and uncover insights that shape customer behaviour and loyalty. In this role, you will partner closely with leaders across our business to identify and prioritise the best opportunities to leverage our data and enable us to deliver various business strategies. You will work directly with the VP of Commercial Finance & FP&A to align data strategy with the company's financial goals and coordinate these with the data platform team, ensuring that every insight translates into a measurable impact on the bottom line. You will think critically about complex challenges in a fast-paced environment. The role requires a blend of analytical experience, business acumen, strong communication and strategic thinking.

What you’ll be doing

You will move beyond static dashboards to lead narrative driven insights through building dashboards and visualisations that support our Performance storytelling, ensuring data is presented with a clear commercial narrative to the business stakeholders and the Board.

Acting as the primary interface between the Commercial team and our data platform, you will translate business problems into more specific questions or hypotheses, and provide/present insights or findings in a subjective manner to relevant stakeholders. 

Identify gaps in the dataset and feed high quality requirements through to data engineering. Triage all business requests as the first port of call. 

Build and manage a team of analysts, mentor and work closely with the team to remove data-related and technical roadblocks. 

Manage analysis work pipeline and prioritisation through collaboration with data scientists, engineers, and cross functional teams. 

Work with Commercial leadership in building quarterly and yearly analytics roadmap.  

Oversee the intake and prioritisation of data requests, ensuring the team focuses on high-value commercial impact rather than just data extraction.

Lead training and provide support for technical and non-technical users on developing charts

Drive a positive team culture, focused on customer outcomes, whilst coaching and developing the technical capabilities of the team

The ideal toolbox

Bachelor or Master degree in Analytics, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Engineering, or other quantitative discipline field with strong academic record.

5+ years of relevant professional experience in analytics or business intelligence roles.

Excellent SQL, proficient knowledge in using SQL, GCP, Excel. Experience in BI tools, like Looker would be an advantage. Experience in Python is advantageous but not required.

Deep commercial acumen with specific experience in e-commerce metrics (CAC, LTV, Contribution Margin, and Inventory Turnover)

Familiarity with financial reporting frameworks and an understanding of how data structures impact financial storytelling.

Expertise in Data Visualization and data storytelling

Experience in team management and/or mentorship

Proven ability to leverage a large dataset, perform in-depth analysis, and present the data and findings that are easily understood by technical and non-technical audiences.

Ability to work to deadlines with good prioritisation, planning and organisational skills.

Autonomous, reliable, with excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively interface with technical and non-technical stakeholders 

Experience working and communicating with distributed and asynchronous teams 

Strong ability to think strategically; You don’t just find bugs, you find opportunities. You are instinctively curious about how data can improve our customer experience and our profitability.

Role location

We believe that building connections and collaborating as Pet Circlers is super important. So this role is based in Sydney with a hybrid arrangement of 3 days per week in our pet friendly offices (your pet might love coming to the office even more than you). This is subject to change in line with business requirements.

Juicy perks

Heaps of development opportunities - stretch projects, secondments and unlimited learning courses via Go1

Flexible working environment

Up to 50% employee discount

Product sample giveaways

Pawrental leave and wellbeing leave

Team charity volunteer days

Classpass subsidy

Why Join?

We reckon our mission to help the world Pet Better is an important one, but also an incredibly fun and rewarding one. Becoming a Pet Circler means you’re committed to help shape an entire industry - it’s pretty exciting stuff. Here’s what we stand for:

We're better together

We operate with humble hearts and hungry minds

Pets matter' so pets and pet parents always have a seat at our table

We're instinctively curious. Always.

Belong at Pet Circle

Our unique perspectives and expertise is our superpower - we value diversity in all forms. So, no matter your background, please apply if this role makes you excited to bring your full self to work each day.

The Data Solutions Designer is a vital part of the Data Services team, who provide trustworthy and safe to use data assets for SEEK teams across APAC, so that they can make informed decisions and deliver customer experiences using data.

Reporting directly to the Engineering Manager, the Data Solution Designer is responsible for designing data assets/products and ensuring they meet the needs of our internal partners and the business.

Job Title: Associate Director Business Governance - Technology, Cyber, Data
Ad Text:
Company description:



ANZ Banking Group Limited



Job description:

About Us

At ANZ, we're shaping a world where people and communities thrive, driven by a common goal: to improve the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our customers. Our Institutional bank helps our largest customers move trade and capital around the region, providing our people with great opportunities to build their technical expertise and their careers.

About the Role

As an Associate Director Business Governance Tech, Info Sec, Data you will provide Tech, Cyber and Data risk management expertise globally for the Division. You will be responsible for working with Enterprise Risk Theme Officers, Business Unit/Country Risk Owners and Business Governance colleagues to determine priority areas of Non-Financial Risk (NFR) uplift across these three critical risk themes; develop and oversight execution of uplift to improve control environments and ensure Divisional compliance with regulatory requirements. The role works across multiple Business Units, Countries, stakeholders and major programs and contributes to embedding uplifted Non-Financial Risk (NFR) practices and behaviours across the Division.

The role suits risk/audit professionals with extensive experience in fast paced, challenging environments and have come from business / technology roles, big 4 or consulting and understand how technology plays into operational risks. The ideal candidate would utilise their business and technology background to translate technology related causes, controls and indicators into business language for inclusion into risks owned by business risk owners.

Role Type: Permanent
Role Location: 833 Collins Street, Docklands VIC 3008
Work Hours: 40 Hours, Full-time

What will your day look like?

As an Associate Director Business Governance Tech, Info Sec, Data, you are accountable for:

Focusing on Technology, Information Security and Data risk themes, lead and drive NFR consistency, alignment and continuous improvement supported by insights and actions to enable well-informed, risk-based decisions.
Partner with business facing BG&C teams, risk and control owners across geographies to become a trusted advisor and maturity uplift lead.
Build and maintain effective working relationships with key stakeholders (such as Group Risk, Group Technology, Australia Retail and Business & Private Bank) across all 3 lines of defence to obtain buy-in to implement consistent uplift
Proactively identify Division wide "hot spots" / areas of concern, completing regular deep dive assessments and developing practical recommendations for inclusion into various governance and oversight bodies.
Lead and facilitate regular, Division wide Community of Practice sessions focused on promoting knowledge sharing, tips and tricks, increasing consistency and continuous improvement.
Drive outcomes across the Division which will ultimately safeguard our customers and ANZ.
Leading multiple streams of work to deliver Institutional NFR priorities
What will you bring?

Strong understanding of Non-Financial Risk management in an Institutional context
Strong understanding and experience with technology related controls (specifically business rules / application computer controls and general computer controls), including control testing
Intermediate to advanced data analysis skills and experience, including sourcing data from disparate sources, producing clear analysis and conclusions / recommendations and practical rationales
Strong cross-functional collaboration skills, relationship building skills and ability to achieve results without direct reporting relationships
Confident communicator with exceptional negotiation and influencing skills. Has a track record in acknowledging and leading resolution of conflict.
Excellent Business and Executive report writing skills, and attention to detail
Project management and delivery management experience in large, complex, dynamic environments
Comfortable working with ambiguity and change
Banking and Finance industry knowledge
Internal / external audit, BG&C / assurance experience
Business process management/ process improvement
Commitment to simplification and driving change
Strong sense of personal responsibility and accountability for delivering high quality work
So why join us?

From the moment you join ANZ, you'll be doing meaningful work that will shape a world where people and communities thrive.

But it's not just our customers who'll feel your impact. You'll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you'll have the resources, opportunities, and support you need to take the next big step in your career.

We're a diverse bunch at ANZ in different roles, different locations, doing different things. That's why we have a range of flexible working arrangements, so our people can 'make work, work for them'. We also provide a range of benefits including access to health and wellbeing services and discounts on selected products and services from ANZ and more.

At ANZ, you'll be part of an organisation where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. That's because we're committed to building a workplace that reflects the diversity of the communities we serve. We welcome applications from everyone and encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you're a candidate with a disability or access requirement, and have an enquiry about the support provided, please let us know on your application or visit ANZ Accessibility and Inclusion Programs for alternate contact methods.

To find out more about working at ANZ, visit https://www.anz.com.au/careers. You can apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 108895 .

Public Skills Australia has been appointed by the Department of Employment and Workplace Relations (DEWR) as one of 10 Jobs and Skills Councils. We work with employer and employee representatives from the Public Safety and Government industry-sectors – Police, Fire and Emergency Services, Correctional Services, Defence, and all levels of Government – to ensure Australia’s vocational education and training (VET) system delivers better outcomes for learners and employers. A primary function of our work is to provide workforce planning, industry intelligence and training product development in support of industry needs and government priorities.

The Manager Workforce Planning and Insights is accountable to the Director Workforce Strategy and Insights and delivers the Public Skills Australia’s Workforce Planning and Research functions. The Manager Workforce Planning and Insights is part of the management team and will oversee the day-to-day management of the Workforce Planning and Insights team. This position will be accountable for the end-to-end planning, management and delivery of successful projects, including reporting, monitoring, and tracking deliverables and milestones and managing budgets and associated risks. While this position reports to the Director they may be required to report to other executive staff depending on the projects they need to manage.

Workforce Planning: This role will lead the development and delivery of annual Workforce Insights Reports by managing a small team of staff dedicated to these deliverables. The delivery of the Workforce Insights Reports required robust desktop and applied research, quantitative analysis of national and industry datasets, qualitative research methods to draw out industry insights and comprehensive consultation of data and findings. The Manager, Workforce Planning and Insights will be responsible for the overarching team planning and project planning to ensure all milestones are met. The Workforce Planning function also requires comprehensive written capability to draft and review extensive reports.

Research: The Manager Workforce Planning and Insights will also oversee a small team of staff dedicated to producing individual research projects that give effect to workforce strategies, ministerial priorities, industry sector requirements and Board directives. This position will oversee the management of a range of project involving analysis of qualitative and quantitative data to deliver research and other project deliverables. They will lead a small team, develop a workplan to deliver projects on the annual Public Skills Australia Business Plan, manage and contract subcontractors, manage their budget and ensure robust consultation, good governance and adherence to federal government requirements.

Responsibilities

In partnership with internal stakeholders and external service providers, with the intent of ensuring compliance with relevant legislative, grant and company compliance obligations, the Manager Workforce Planning and Insights will:

• Manage the Workforce Planning and Insights team, including HR activities (probations, performance reviews, professional development, WHS and other requirements) and ensure appropriate professional behaviour in line with the company values.

• Develop and deliver the annual business plan for the team, meeting quality, governance and consultation expectations and processes.

• Oversee the development and completion of high-quality reports, plans by leading research, data analysis and the development of insights and findings that meets the expectations of their executive.

• Undertake thorough industry consultation through various engagement and research methods, including workshop facilitation.

• Maintain productive relationships with internal and external stakeholders, often at a senior and executive level demonstrating strong political acumen and corporate maturity.

• Manage and contribute to relevant stakeholder networks and/or governance groups (as determined by business need) by supporting the Chair, engaging with members of the group and contributing to all aspects of their meetings and meeting preparation.

• Undertake end-to-end project management of Workforce Insights Reports and Research deliverables, by scoping, planning, managing, and monitoring project plans.

• Manage budgets, ensuring good fiscal practice and risks are proactively identified and mitigated.

• Undertake procurement processes and manage subcontractors to support the delivery of individual research projects and other business plan items.

• Manage a team, including probations, performance and other human resource requirements.

• Proactively brief their Director and Executive on the progress of projects, along with any opportunities, challenges, risks and solutions.

• Present to a variety of audiences (including executives) using excellent written and verbal communication skills.

• Work collaboratively with other areas of the business, relevant Managers and other members of staff.

• Any other reasonable duties as required.

Key Selection Criteria – Essential

• Demonstrated experience leading and managing teams and subcontractors in a complex, changing, and busy environment to deliver successful outcomes whilst exhibiting professional behaviour in line with organisational values. 

• Ability to develop and motivate staff and develop a high-performance culture.

• A Higher Education qualification such as a relevant Bachelor’s or Master’s degree.

• Experience with complex research methodologies and policy skills at a senior level in an applied setting.

• Excellent written and verbal communications skills.

• Demonstrated capability to negotiate and build consensus with internal and external stakeholders.

• Proven ability to facilitate workshops and deliver engaging presentations.

• Operate with a high level of political acumen and corporate maturity to build relationship with senior and executive level stakeholders.

• Experience in project management, planning and budgetary practices.

• Ability to manage contracts, using established procurement processes.

• Motivated to drive a positive can-do culture across the company.

• Proven capability work on multiple products in a fast-paced environment.

• Strong interpersonal skills, with a motivation and preparedness to support the Executive of the organisation.

Key Selection Criteria – Desirable

• Experience working within the Public Safety and Government industry sectors.

• Experience in workforce planning, policy development AND/OR strategic foresight AND/OR environmental scanning.

How to apply

Your application must include a CV/Resume of no more than 4 pages and a Cover Letter of no more than 2 pages. The Cover Letter should not repeat information contained in the CV but specifically address the ‘essential’ Key Selection Criteria. Any queries should be directed to the HR Team at careers@publicskillsaustralia.org.au. Applications close at midnight, Sunday 1 February 2026.

Applications will be processed as they are received, interviews and appointment may occur before the end date.

Job Title: Data Governance Analyst- Billing & Data Quality Focus
Ad Text:
We’re recruiting a Data Governance Analyst for a large, complex organisation undergoing significant transformation within its billing and customer data environment.

This is a Contract until June 30th, 2026 - there may be an extension
Hybrid | 3 days p/w on site | Melbourne | Day rate | Parking nearby

This is not a purely strategic or advisory governance role. It’s a hands-on position for someone who enjoys getting into messy data, asking the hard questions, and working closely with the business to fix real problems.
If you’re the kind of person who likes understanding why data is broken, explaining it clearly to non-technical teams, and then helping put the fix in place — this role will suit you.

What you’ll be doing
This role is approximately 50/50 hands-on delivery and stakeholder engagement.

You will:

Monitor, track and report on data quality metrics and issues
Conduct root cause analysis on data issues and recommend practical remediation actions
Work with business teams to clean up data and prevent repeat issues
Define, document and maintain data definitions, metadata and business glossaries
Build and maintain Power BI dashboards and regular operational reporting
Use advanced Excel and SQL daily (some scripting/coding experience is highly desirable)
Support the development of data standards, governance processes and roadmaps
Work closely with delivery teams on a high-profile billing program
What the hiring team is really looking for
They are prioritising communication and mindset just as much as technical capability.

You’ll be successful if you:

Can confidently explain Data Governance to people who don’t work in data
Can explain metadata and data quality issues in plain English
Are comfortable having frequent conversations across the business 
Are inquisitive, ask “why”, and dig deeper into issues
Can work independently once given direction (no hand-holding)
Stay positive and solutions-focused in complex, high-pressure environments
Essential experience
Hands-on experience implementing or operating data governance practices
Strong experience with data quality monitoring, reporting and issue management
Proven root cause analysis experience on data issues
Metadata management, data definitions, business glossaries and documentation
Advanced Excel, strong SQL, and Power BI dashboarding
Experience working with billing, customer, financial or transactional data
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills
Experience working in utilities, financial services, government or large enterprise environments
Highly regarded
Certification in Data Governance or Data Management (e.g. CDMP, CDPSE, DCAM)
Experience stepping into “fix it” roles where things are already live and imperfect
Why this role?
You’ll have real ownership and impact
You’ll work with a passionate, collaborative data leader who values open communication
You’ll help stabilise and improve a critical billing and customer data environment
This is a role for someone who wants to add value quickly, not sit on the sidelines
If this sounds like you, apply now or reach out to me at Lfrank@launchrecruitment.com.au for a confidential conversation.

If you’re more strategy-focused or prefer minimal stakeholder interaction, this role is unlikely to be the right fit — and that’s completely okay.

Job Title: Hybrid Senior Business Analyst / Data Analyst
Ad Text:
We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst / Data Analyst to join a major, business-led transformation initiative within a complex enterprise environment. This role sits at the intersection of business analysis and data analysis and will play a critical part in shaping future-state processes, systems, and data platforms, particularly within large technology and customer migrations.

You will work closely with senior stakeholders, delivery teams, and technology partners to define, analyse, and deliver high-quality requirements and data outcomes that drive measurable business value.

The role

This position involves detailed business and data analysis across large, complex programs of work. You will be responsible for end-to-end requirements management, data analysis activities, and contributing to solution design and delivery.

Data analysis responsibilities:


* Extract data from multiple source systems to support analysis and delivery activities
* Perform data profiling to support system and customer migrations
* Map and document data sources, structures, and fields from legacy to target systems
* Review data to identify anomalies and determine whether they represent business scenarios or data quality issues

Business analysis responsibilities:


* Elicit, analyse, validate, and document business requirements across products, processes, policies, systems, and data
* Partner with stakeholders to define and manage requirements through the full delivery lifecycle
* Provide clear, evidence-based recommendations that support strategic business outcomes
* Conduct gap analysis between current and future states and recommend high-value solutions
* Support solution design through data-driven insights and analysis

What you'll bring:

Core capabilities
* Strong analytical mindset with the ability to anticipate issues and plan strategically
* Methodical problem-solver who can translate complexity into practical, high-impact solutions
* Self-starter with the ability to work independently in complex environments
* Excellent stakeholder engagement, communication, and influencing skills
* Strong business acumen, including the ability to distinguish true data quality issues from valid business scenarios

Technical and professional expertise
* Proven experience in data extraction, analysis, mapping, and profiling
* Strong understanding of technology platforms and business systems
* Solid grounding in project delivery methodologies and best practices
* Experience working on large, complex transformation or migration programs
* Experience with mortgage or financial services systems is highly desirable

Key responsibilities

Accountability and ownership
* Take ownership of outcomes and proactively address gaps or risks
* Resolve conflicts constructively while maintaining alignment with shared goals

Stakeholder engagement
* Build strong relationships with senior and operational stakeholders
* Clearly communicate complex concepts, decisions, and outcomes in both written and verbal form
* Secure buy-in for proposed solutions through structured analysis and evidence

Project delivery and requirements management
* Independently plan and execute analysis activities across large programs
* Produce high-quality, traceable, and approved requirements documentation
* Manage requirement changes to ensure alignment with scope, timelines, and strategy

Risk and governance
* Identify, escalate, and manage project and operational risks in line with governance frameworks

Performance measures

Success in this role will be measured across areas including:
* Accuracy, completeness, and traceability of requirements
* Achievement of defined business objectives
* Stakeholder satisfaction and engagement
* Continuity of business operations during change
* Realisation of expected benefits and customer outcomes

Full-time, Brisbane or Sydney based hybrid role

Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

What you’ll be doing

As a Senior Data Scientist specialising in the application of Large Language Models, you’ll design and deliver production-ready LLM-based systems that solve real business problems. This role combines deep expertise in Applied AI with the practical engineering skills that are needed to build, evaluate and optimise LLM-based solutions.

Key responsibilities include:

Design end-to-end LLM-based solutions including retrieval, prompting, fine-tuning, and tool/API integration.
Build and iterate on retrieval-augmented generation pipelines (document ingestion, embeddings, vector search, reranking, context assembly).
Design and implement agentic workflows for multi-step reasoning and tool usage.
Write production-quality Python code to integrate LLM systems into business applications and workflows.
Optimise systems for latency, reliability, and cost using caching, batching, and inference optimisation.

Company description:



Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:


Be a part of a major transformation in investment administration with real impact across systems and platforms.
Work on high-profile projects in a collaborative, agile, and business-led environment.
Shape the future of superannuation technology while growing your leadership and domain expertise.

The opportunity to join our team


Are you ready to lead one of the most significant investment administration transformations in Australia's superannuation sector?



At Insignia Financial, we're embarking on a multi-year journey to simplify and modernise our investment systems — and we're looking for a Senior Business Analyst to help us make it happen. This is your chance to work on high-impact initiatives that will define the future of our proprietary platforms and improve outcomes for millions of Australians.



You'll be joining a passionate, collaborative team leading a major transformation of our investment administration systems, focused on consolidating platforms, enhancing our proprietary UNISON system, and designing a new, future-ready pricing model.



As a Senior Business Analyst, you'll play a key role in shaping and delivering this transformation. You'll work closely with business stakeholders, delivery leads, and technology teams to:

Lead business and system analysis across discovery, development, testing, and delivery phases.
Translate complex business needs into clear, actionable user stories and acceptance criteria.
Support UAT and functionality testing, ensuring solutions meet business expectations.
Partner with product owners to define value, prioritise requirements, and articulate the product vision.
Coach and support other analysts, lifting capability across the team.
Navigate ambiguity and drive clarity in a fast-paced, evolving environment.


You'll be working on projects that include:

Consolidating four registry systems into one.
Consolidating from 3 unit pricing systems to 1.
Defining a new, flexible pricing model - the biggest uplift in UNISON in 20 years.
Supporting the migration of off-platform funds into UNISON.
Contributing to cost optimisation and scale initiatives aligned to our MasterTrust roadmap.

What You Bring to This Role


To thrive in this role, you'll need to bring a strong mix of domain expertise, analytical leadership, and delivery experience. Specifically, we're looking for:

Deep experience in Business Analysis within a software development team, ideally within superannuation or investment administration.
Firm understanding of:
Fund administration & accounting
Unit pricing and distributions
Custody services and general ledger accounting
Investment platforms like pControl, HiPortfolio, and UNISON (preferred, not essential)
Experience in technology transformation programs, especially platform migrations.
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills.
Agile delivery experience and comfort working with ambiguity.
Certifications like CBAP, AAC, or Scrum Master are a plus.

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward. Along the way, you'll be free to explore new ideas and technology, solve problems in a team, and independently to get great things done. Around here, we like to call it "putting our fingerprints on the future".

People-inspired tech

Deep expertise combined with creativity can take on the trickiest of problems. Join our team of brilliant minds and mentors as we explore our way to innovation and apply technology in more human ways than ever.

__

To Apply

Read more here about why you should join our team.

Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and at a minimum be required to undertake police and basic credit checks as a condition of employment.

Please note that applications from agencies will not be considered at this time.

We acknowledge and celebrate the richness that individual differences bring to our team. If you need assistance or an adjustment during the application process, please reach out and let us know.

Your new opportunity 
Take on a meaningful leadership role in shaping Queensland's social policy under the Social Policy and Analytics branch of Queensland Treasury. As the Principal Treasury Analyst, you will provide expert advice and oversight of critical social policy frameworks and initiatives, supporting government-wide priorities and championing evidence-based decision-making for the benefit of Queensland communities.  

Set in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, this role offers the opportunity to create impactful solutions that address complex policy challenges. Join us and bring your expertise to the forefront of Queensland's strategic policy agenda.

In this role, you will: 
•    Lead and coordinate the delivery of a complex program of social policy analysis and initiatives. 
•    Develop and deliver strategic, practical, and solutions-focused advice on social policy frameworks and programs to internal and external stakeholders, ensuring alignment with the government's priorities. 
•    Exercise sound judgment, provide authoritative advice, and influence stakeholders to balance client needs and team goals. 
•    Offer leadership and direction to team members executing multi-dimensional projects, while delivering guidance and support to senior executives and clients. 
•    Build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders to address challenging and complex policy issues. 
•    Represent Queensland Treasury in high-level consultations, negotiations, and forums—ensuring consistent and professional advocacy of policy priorities.

What experience you will bring: 
•    Demonstrated experience in program and project management or in advancing proactive, evidence-based policy agendas across multi-disciplinary teams. 
•    A strong ability to prepare and deliver strategic and actionable policy advice. 
•    A desire and proven ability to inspire meaningful change and drive policy outcomes. 
•    Highly effective communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to tailor messaging to diverse stakeholders and audiences. 
•    Strong interpersonal and relationship management skills, fostering collaboration and information sharing among stakeholders.

Whilst there are no mandatory qualifications needed for this role, relevant qualifications will be highly regarded.  

How to apply

•    Your resume detailing relevant experience 
•    A cover letter of no more than two pages outlining why you are interested in this position and how your knowledge, skills and experience makes you a strong candidate for the role.
